fields.name: DefaultSampleModel
fields.description: Specifies the model of sample that will be used if this model is specified to be used in an experiment.

fields.name: MolecularFormula
fields.description: Chemical formula of this molecule (e.g. H2O, NH2, etc.).

fields.name: DetectionLabel
fields.description: Indicates whether this molecule (e.g. Alexa Fluor 488) can be attached to another molecule and act as a tag that can indicate the presence and amount of the other molecule.

fields.name: AffinityLabel
fields.description: Indicates whether this molecule has high binding capacity with certain material and can be attached to another molecule (e.g. His Tag).

fields.name: DetectionLabels
fields.description: Indicates the tags (e.g. Alexa Fluor 488) that the molecule contains, which can indicate the presence and amount of the molecule.

fields.name: AffinityLabels
fields.description: Indicates the tags that the molecule contains (e.g. His Tag), which has high binding capacity with other materials.

fields.name: Targets
fields.description: Target molecules (e.g. proteins or antibodies) to which this molecule binds selectively.

fields.name: State
fields.description: The physical state of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: Density
fields.description: The density of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: ExtinctionCoefficients
fields.description: A measure of how strongly this molecule absorbs light at a particular wavelength.

fields.name: Fluorescent

FluorescenceExcitation
Maximums

fields.name: MolecularWeight
fields.description: The molecular weight of this molecule (the mass of one mole of the molecule).

fields.name: ExactMass
fields.description: The most abundant mass of the molecule calculated using the natural abundance of isotopes on Earth.

fields.name: StructureImageFile
fields.description: An image depicting the molecule's chemical structure.

fields.name: StructureFile
fields.description: A file that contains the molecule's chemical structure.

fields.name: MeltingPoint
fields.description: Melting temperature of a pure sample of this molecule at atmospheric pressure.

fields.name: BoilingPoint
fields.description: Temperature at which a pure sample of this molecule boils under atmospheric pressure.

fields.name: VaporPressure
fields.description: Vapor pressure of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature.

fields.name: Viscosity
fields.description: The viscosity of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature.

fields.name: pKa
fields.description: The logarithmic acid dissociation constants of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature.

fields.name: NMRSolventPeak
fields.description: The known chemical shift for a given nucleus for this molecule.

fields.name: Chiral
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule is a enantiomer, that cannot be superposed on its mirror image by any combination of rotations and translations.

fields.name: Racemic
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule represents equal amounts of left- and right-handed enantiomers of a chiral molecule.

fields.name: EnantiomerForms
fields.description: If this molecule is racemic (Racemic -> True), indicates models for its left- and right-handed enantiomers.

fields.name: RacemicForm
fields.description: If this molecule is one of the enantiomers (Chiral -> True), indicates the model for its racemic form.

fields.name: EnantiomerPair
fields.description: If this molecule is one of the enantiomers (Chiral -> True), indicates the model for its non-superimposable mirror imaged molecule (stereoisomer).

fields.name: pH
fields.description: The logarithmic concentration of hydrogen ions of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: Radioactive
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule emits substantial ionizing radiation.

fields.name: Ventilated
fields.description: Indicates if a pure sample of this molecule must be handled in a ventilated enclosures.

fields.name: Flammable
fields.description: Indicates if a pure sample of this molecule is easily set aflame at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: Acid
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule are strong acids (pH <= 2).

fields.name: Base
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule are strong acids (pH >= 12).

fields.name: Pyrophoric
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule can ignite spontaneously upon exposure to air.

fields.name: WaterReactive
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule react spontaneously upon exposure to water.

fields.name: Fuming
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule emit fumes spontaneously when exposed to air.

fields.name: HazardousBan
fields.description: Indicates this molecule is currently banned from usage in the ECL because the facility isn't yet equiped to handle it.

fields.name: ExpirationHazard
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule become hazardous once they are expired and must be automatically disposed of when they pass their expiration date.

fields.name:
ParticularlyHazardous
Substance
fields.description: Indicates if special precautions should be taken in handling this molecule, as indicated by the MSDS classification.

fields.name: DrainDisposal
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule may be safely disposed down a standard drain.

fields.name: Pungent
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule have a strong odor.

fields.name: MSDSRequired
fields.description: Indicates if an MSDS is required for this molecule.

fields.name: MSDSFile
fields.description: The PDF of the MSDS (Materials Saftey Data Sheet) of this molecule.

fields.name: NFPA

fields.name: DOTHazardClass

fields.name: BiosafetyLevel

fields.name: LightSensitive

fields.name: IncompatibleMaterials

fields.name: LiquidHandlerIncompatible
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule cannot be reliably aspirated or dispensed on an automated liquid handling robot.

fields.name: PipettingMethod

fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule cannot be performed via the ultrasonic distance method due to vapors interfering with the reading.
